Bootstrap: docker
From: mambaorg/micromamba:1.5.8-jammy

%labels
    Version         1.3.0
    Description     Variant Annotator for PGS/PRS Platform — VEP-lite HPC-native annotation
    GFF3_Reference  /ref/gencode.annotation.gff3     (bind-mount at runtime)
    FASTA_Reference /fasta/hg38.fa                   (bind-mount at runtime)
    dbNSFP5_Path    /dbnsfp/dbNSFP5.0a_grch38.gz     (bind-mount at runtime)
    dbSNP_Freq_Path /dbsnp_freq/freq.vcf.gz           (bind-mount at runtime)
    Build_Date      2026-04-13
    Changes_v1.3    dbSNP population frequency support (rsid, af_global, af_max_population,
                    af_population_summary, rarity_class) via dbsnp_freq.py.
                    Complementary to dbNSFP5 — both can be used simultaneously.
    Changes_v1.2    FASTA-backed coding consequences (missense/synonymous/stop/frameshift),
                    splice donor/acceptor via GT/AG inspection, dbNSFP5 scores
                    (CADD/REVEL/SIFT/PolyPhen2/ClinVar), pysam added.

%help
    Variant Annotator container for the PGS/PRS Platform (v1.3).

    Annotates betamap variants using GENCODE GFF3. Produces:
      {PGS_ID}_variants_annotated.tsv.gz
      {PGS_ID}_variants_annotated.parquet
      {PGS_ID}_annotation_summary.json

    v1.3 new features (requires --dbsnp):
      - Population allele frequencies from dbSNP freq.vcf.gz (tabix-indexed)
      - New columns: rsid, af_global, af_max_population, af_population_summary, rarity_class
      - Rarity classification: common / low_frequency / rare / ultra_rare / novel
      - Complementary to dbNSFP5 — both sources can be used simultaneously

    v1.2 new features (requires --fasta and/or --dbnsfp):
      - Coding consequences from FASTA: missense, synonymous, stop_gained,
        stop_lost, start_lost, frameshift, inframe_insertion, inframe_deletion
      - Splice donor vs acceptor classified by GT/AG FASTA inspection
      - REF allele verified against reference FASTA
      - dbNSFP5 scores: CADD_phred, REVEL_score, SIFT_pred, Polyphen2_HDIV_pred,
        clinvar_clnsig via --dbnsfp
      - Boolean consequence flags: is_missense, is_synonymous, is_lof

    v1.1 features:
      - Splice site distance (distance_to_splice_site column)
      - Splice site / splice region consequence reclassification
      - All overlapping genes + transcripts (all_overlapping_genes, etc.)
      - Regulatory BED file support via --regulatory-bed
      - Consequence priority numeric ranking (consequence_priority)

    Full v1.3 run (via wrapper script):
      DATA_DIR=/path/to/scores \
      ANNOTATIONS_DIR=/path/to/annotations \
      GFF3_PATH=/path/to/gencode.annotation.gff3 \
      SIF_PATH=/path/to/variant_annotator.sif \
      FASTA_PATH=/path/to/hg38.fa \
      DBNSFP_PATH=/path/to/dbNSFP5.0a_grch38.gz \
      DBSNP_FREQ_PATH=/path/to/freq.vcf.gz \
      /path/to/annotator/run_annotation.sh PGS000001

    Direct run:
      apptainer exec \
        --bind /path/to/scores/PGS000001:/data/PGS000001:ro \
        --bind /path/to/gencode:/ref:ro \
        --bind /path/to/fasta:/fasta:ro \
        --bind /path/to/dbnsfp:/dbnsfp:ro \
        --bind /path/to/annotations:/annotations:rw \
        --bind /path/to/annotator:/app/annotator:ro \
        variant_annotator.sif \
        python /app/annotator/annotate_variants.py \
          --betamap /data/PGS000001/PGS000001_hmPOS_GRCh38.betamap.tsv.gz \
          --gff3    /ref/gencode.annotation.gff3 \
          --outdir  /annotations/PGS000001 \
          --pgs-id  PGS000001 \
          --fasta   /fasta/hg38.fa \
          --dbnsfp  /dbnsfp/dbNSFP5.0a_grch38.gz

%environment
    export LANG=C.UTF-8
    export LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
    export MAMBA_ROOT_PREFIX=/opt/conda
    export PATH=/opt/conda/bin:${PATH}
    export PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1
    export PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1

%post
    # ── System packages ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    apt-get update -qq && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        build-essential \
        libz-dev \
        liblzma-dev \
        libbz2-dev \
        pigz \
        && apt-get clean && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # ── Conda environment ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    # Install Python + scientific stack via conda-forge (pre-compiled binaries)
    micromamba install -y -n base -c conda-forge \
        python=3.12 \
        pandas=2.2 \
        numpy=1.26 \
        pyarrow=15 \
        tqdm=4.66 \
        && micromamba clean -afy

    # ── Pure-Python packages via pip ──────────────────────────────────────────
    # pyfaidx: random-access FASTA reader for coding-consequence annotation
    # pysam:   tabix interface for dbNSFP5 queries
    /opt/conda/bin/pip install --no-cache-dir \
        intervaltree==3.1.0 \
        polars==0.20.18 \
        pyfaidx==0.8.1.2 \
        pysam==0.22.1

    # ── Create standard bind-mount stubs ─────────────────────────────────────
    # These will be overlaid by --bind at runtime.
    mkdir -p /data /ref /fasta /dbnsfp /dbsnp_freq /regulatory /annotations /app/annotator

    # ── Validate install ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/opt/conda/bin/python - <<'PY'
import pandas, numpy, pyarrow, intervaltree, tqdm, pyfaidx, pysam
print('pandas',      pandas.__version__)
print('numpy',       numpy.__version__)
print('pyarrow',     pyarrow.__version__)
print('intervaltree OK')
print('tqdm',        tqdm.__version__)
print('pyfaidx',     pyfaidx.__version__)
print('pysam',       pysam.__version__)
print('All packages OK')
PY

%runscript
    # Default: show usage when the image is run without exec
    echo "Variant Annotator v1.2  (PGS/PRS Platform)"
    echo ""
    echo "Usage:"
    echo "  apptainer exec [bind options] variant_annotator.sif \\"
    echo "    python /app/annotator/annotate_variants.py \\"
    echo "      --betamap  /data/PGS000001/PGS000001_hmPOS_GRCh38.betamap.tsv.gz \\"
    echo "      --gff3     /ref/gencode.v49.basic.annotation.gff3 \\"
    echo "      --outdir   /annotations/PGS000001 \\"
    echo "      --pgs-id   PGS000001 \\"
    echo "      [--fasta   /fasta/hg38.fa] \\"
    echo "      [--dbnsfp  /dbnsfp/dbNSFP5.0a_grch38.gz] \\"
    echo "      [--regulatory-bed /regulatory/encode_cCRE.bed.gz ...]"
    echo ""
    echo "See: docs/VARIANT_ANNOTATION.md"

%test
    # Smoke-test: check Python and key packages are importable
    /opt/conda/bin/python -c "
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import pyarrow as pa
from intervaltree import IntervalTree
from tqdm import tqdm
import pyfaidx
import pysam

# IntervalTree functionality test
t = IntervalTree()
t[0:100] = 'test'
assert len(t[50]) == 1, 'IntervalTree query failed'

# Simulate annotator imports
import sys
sys.path.insert(0, '/app/annotator')
try:
    from gff3_parser import GFF3Index, GFF3Feature
    from classify import classify, AnnotationResult, CONSEQUENCE_PRIORITY
    from regulatory import RegulatoryBEDIndex
    from sequence_utils import translate_codon, snp_codon_consequence, is_lof_consequence

    # Quick classify smoke test
    result = classify([])
    assert result.region_class == 'intergenic', 'classify intergenic failed'
    assert result.consequence  == 'intergenic_variant'
    assert not result.is_lof

    # Regulatory BED index
    reg = RegulatoryBEDIndex()
    assert reg.is_empty

    # Sequence utils
    assert translate_codon('ATG') == 'M'
    assert snp_codon_consequence('ATG', 'TTG', 0) == 'start_lost'
    assert is_lof_consequence('stop_gained')
    assert not is_lof_consequence('synonymous_variant')

    # v1.2 fields on AnnotationResult
    assert hasattr(result, 'codon_ref')
    assert hasattr(result, 'is_lof')
    assert hasattr(result, 'cadd_phred')

    print('Annotator module imports OK')
    print('sequence_utils smoke test OK')
    print('v1.2 AnnotationResult fields OK')
except ImportError as e:
    print(f'Annotator import skipped (not mounted at test time): {e}')

print('Smoke test PASSED')
"
